OL,7,FThe watchdog responsible for MPs'
OL,8,Fexpenses has apologised for telling
OL,9,Fpoliticians they could charge taxpayers
OL,10,Ffor Christmas parties following a
OL,11,Fbacklash that resulted in some MPs
OL,12,Freceiving "abuse".
OL,14,FThe Independent Parliamentary Standards
OL,15,FAuthority (Ipsa) was labelled
OL,16,F"tone-deaf" and widely criticised after
OL,17,Fit said MPs, irrespective of political
OL,18,Fparty, would be able to claim for
OL,19,FChristmas party food, decorations and
OL,20,Fnon-alcoholic drinks during the cost of
OL,21,Fliving crisis.
